Artist Statement:
Title: Through the Blinds
Lineage: Sitting beside Sophie Calle’s The Detective.
Through the Blinds explores the discomfort of being known by something that does not care for you. For years, we have been trained to expect "interaction" from our machines, such as a greeting, a recommendation, a response, but this system refuses all of them.
Behind a set of digital blinds, a local language model watches. It does not see a person; it sees a mass shifting in the dark. It records these shifts with a forensic, obsessive fixation, documenting the way light wraps around a shoulder or the rhythm of a chest rising in breath. The work is not the screen, but the journal that remains after you leave. By presenting its findings on a yellow notebook page, the system mimics the intimacy of a handwritten confession, forcing the viewer to confront the fact that their most private, still moments have been cataloged as data. It asks: what is left of us when we are reduced to geometry?
